		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">ii</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>







	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="H1" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><A NAME="T13"></A><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">PROSPECTUS SUMMARY</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">The following summary highlights information contained elsewhere in this prospectus or incorporated by reference in this prospectus, and does not contain all of the information that you need to consider in making your investment decision. We urge you to read this entire prospectus (as supplemented or amended), including our consolidated financial statements, notes to the consolidated financial statements and other information incorporated by reference in this prospectus from our other filings with the SEC, before making an investment decision.</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Company Overview</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">We are a leading Web 3.0 infrastructure and product solution provider, specialized in the development of HTC&#x00a0;chips and HPC chips. We have built a comprehensive FPU architecture which offers solution that integrates the features of both HTC and HPC.&#x00a0;In addition, we have actively positioned ourselves in the digital assets space, starting to adopt BNB as our primary reserve asset in July 2025. As of September&#x00a0;26, 2025, we have accumulated nearly US$122<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>million in BNB and US$65<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>million in BTC.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">We plan to further strengthen our BNB strategic reserve through multiple approaches, including continued accumulation of BNB, acquisition of controlling stakes in BNB<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-focused</FONT> strategic reserve entities, and investment in companies dedicated to holding BNB as a core reserve asset.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">We have established an integrated solution platform covering two main&#x00a0;business verticals, including HTC solutions and HPC solutions. Our HTC solutions feature our proprietary&#x00a0;Cuckoo&#x00a0;series chips, which have become alternative ASICs solutions for traditional GPUs. Our HPC solutions offer both HPC chips,&#x00a0;Darkbird, and Bitcoin mining machine,&#x00a0;iPollo. In addition to HTC and HPC chips, we launched our&#x00a0;Darksteel&#x00a0;series, which can be applied to both industrial and commercial sectors by offering distributed computing and data storage solutions, in the fourth quarter of 2021.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">For a description of our business, financial condition, results of operations and other important information regarding us, see our filings with the SEC incorporated by reference herein. For instructions on how to find copies of these and our other filings incorporated by reference in the accompanying prospectus, see &#x201c;Where You Can Find More Information About Us&#x201d; in this prospectus.</P>
		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Overview of BNB</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">BNB functions as the core utility and governance token within the BNB chain ecosystem (BNB Chain), supporting diversified use cases primarily including decentralized finance (DeFi), centralized finance (CeFi), and payment solutions (PayFi). BNB operates as a multifunctional, scalable blockchain infrastructure token essential to BNB Chain&#x2019;s ecosystem operations and innovation. BNB may be utilized to enable transaction fee payments, staking/governance participation, liquid staking derivatives, CeFi privileges, real<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-world</FONT> payments, decentralized storage, and financial services, while supporting ecosystem growth through validator rewards and protocol governance.</P>
		<P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">BNB Token Supply Mechanisms</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">BNB was launched in 2017 with an initial total supply of 200&#x00a0;million tokens. The protocol operates a deflationary model that progressively reduces supply. As of July&#x00a0;2025 following the 32<FONT CLASS="Superscript" STYLE="vertical-align:super;font-size:58%;">nd</FONT> quarterly burn event, BNB&#x2019;s total supply stood at approximately 139.29&#x00a0;million tokens.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">For the token generation mechanism, BNB implements zero post<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-launch</FONT> token minting, eliminating inflationary mechanisms. Supply reduction occurs exclusively through burning. Cross<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT> transfers between BNB Smart Chain (BSC) and BNB Greenfield utilize lock/unlock protocols, and there is no new token creation for BNB.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">For the burn mechanism, BNB employs two primary burn mechanisms, including (1)&#x00a0;auto<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-burn</FONT>, which executes algorithmic quarterly burns based on BNB market price and BSC block production metrics, which constitutes an auditable, transparent on<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT> process independent of centralized exchanges, and (2)&#x00a0;real<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-time</FONT> burn, which destroys a portion of BSC gas fees per block where governance mechanisms determine the burn ratio, dynamically adjusting according to network activity.</P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">1</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">In addition, BNB operates as a deflationary token. The auto<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-burn</FONT> and real<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-time</FONT> burn mechanisms systematically reduce total supply. There is no inflation mechanism for BNB, as it prohibits new token creation.</P>
		<P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">BNB Ecosystem</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The BNB ecosystem comprises multiple blockchains, including BSC, opBNB (Layer<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-2</FONT> scaling solution), and BNB Greenfield (decentralized storage network), collectively establishing infrastructure supporting Web3, DeFi, AI, and data tokenization innovations. BNB serves as the core utility token enabling payment fees, staking, governance, storage, and real<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-world</FONT> transactions across this ecosystem.</P>
		<P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">BNB Lifecycle</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">BNB commenced its lifecycle with a genesis event in 2017, launching via an initial coin offering where 200&#x00a0;million tokens were minted. It initially existed as an Ethereum ERC<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-20</FONT> token before migrating to become the native token of BNB Chain. The protocol explicitly prohibits the creation of any new tokens after this genesis event.</P>
		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Our Cryptocurrency Holdings</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">In 2024, we acquired a total of approximately 361 Bitcoins with an average purchase price of approximately US$99,765 per Bitcoin, inclusive of fees and expenses. We did not sell any Bitcoin in 2024. From January&#x00a0;1, 2025 to April&#x00a0;10, 2025, we acquired a total of approximately 40 Bitcoins with an average purchase price of approximately US$97,565 per Bitcoin, inclusive of fees and expenses.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">In 2024, we also acquired and sold a total of approximately 4.1&#x00a0;million USDTs. Transactions involving USDT were generally valued based on a 1:1 exchange rate with the U.S.&#x00a0;dollar.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">As of December&#x00a0;31, 2024, we carried US$33.8&#x00a0;million of cryptocurrencies on our balance sheet, consisting of approximately 361 Bitcoins and 9 USDTs, reflecting US$2.2&#x00a0;million unrealized loss on changes in fair value of cryptocurrencies, attributable to Bitcoin trading price fluctuations.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">As of September&#x00a0;26, 2025, we held approximately 600 Bitcoins, 128,000 BNBs and 1,569,631 USDTs. As of September&#x00a0;26, 2025, at 4:00&#x00a0;p.m. Eastern Time, the market price of one Bitcoin reported on Binance was US$109,172.21, and the market price of one BNB reported on Binance was US$954.81.</P>
		<P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Custody of our Cryptocurrency Holdings</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">We maintain our cryptocurrency holdings in wallets hosted on reputable exchanges and custodians, currently including Binance and CEFFU.&#x00a0;The selection of these exchanges involves a careful evaluation of their security measures, regulatory compliance, and requires approval by our senior management. When establishing new wallets, an operational representative and two additional reviewers are required to be physically present. Wallet passwords are set and securely maintained by one designated reviewer. We employ a robust &#x201c;3<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of-2</FONT>&#x201d; multi<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-signature</FONT> security arrangement to enhance protection, requiring multiple authorized signatures to authorize transactions. Hardware wallets are securely stored in dedicated safes. Software wallets are utilized strictly as transitional platforms, facilitating individual incoming and outgoing transactions without retaining balances, thereby minimizing exposure and enhancing security. Our auditor performs annual procedures in compliance with PCAOB rules, including existence verification, to reasonably assure the balance of our cryptocurrency assets reported in the consolidated balance sheets are free of material misstatement.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Nearly 35.0% of our cryptocurrency assets is custodied by CEFFU, a secure and independent institutional custody platform specializing in virtual asset safekeeping. Operating as an independent entity, CEFFU maintains rigorous security protocols, compliance standards, and governance frameworks. For our cryptocurrency assets stored in CEFFU, we are not aware of the proportion of private keys that are held in hot, warm or cold storage. The&#x00a0;cryptocurrency holdings stored by the CEFFU are completely segregated and verifiable on<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT>. CEFFU has SOC&#x00a0;II Type&#x00a0;II audits from its auditor to ensure the security of our cryptocurrency assets. Specifically, CEFFU utilizes multi<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-party</FONT> computation technology to eliminate single points of private key vulnerability. By distributing key shares across FIPS&#x00a0;140<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-2</FONT> compliant hardware security modules with strict non<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-exportability</FONT> controls, this cryptographic architecture ensures end<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-to</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-end</FONT> protection against key compromise. However, CEFFU does not provide insurance on client assets under custody. Instead, CEFFU maintains its own internal risk management and asset allocation policies. </P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">2</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;text-indent:0pt;margin-top:8pt;">See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We maintain our cryptocurrency assets with third<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-party</FONT> custodians or exchanges that do not carry insurance or do not disclose whether carrying insurance for any losses of the cryptocurrency assets, exposing us to a material loss of these assets in the event of a security breach, operational failure, or insolvency of such custodian.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Per our agreement with CEFFU, we are obligated to provide and maintain current and precise KYC/AML documentation. CEFFU conducts rigorous identity verification, continuously monitors transactions for suspicious activity, and adheres strictly to anti<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-money</FONT> laundering regulations. Fees for services are detailed in a separate fee letter and may be adjusted by CEFFU with prior notice to us. Either party may terminate the agreement with thirty&#x00a0;days&#x2019; written notice. In addition, CEFFU retains the unilateral right to immediately suspend or close accounts in cases of material breaches, fraudulent activities, regulatory enforcement actions, or violations of AML requirements.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Our remaining cryptocurrency assets are maintained by Binance, which is an online exchange and a trading platform for digital assets trading. Binance does not make custodian arrangements publicly available according to its internal policy. As a result, we lack visibility into the custody arrangements, including how the private key is stored, and whether Binance maintains insurance coverage for our holdings. We have a standard agreement with Binance which stipulates, among others, that our cryptocurrency assets held by Binance are not segregated on<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT> in different wallets from cryptocurrency assets held on behalf of other users. According to the standard agreement, Binance uses an internal ledger to record customer entitlements to the quantity and type of digital assets. Each user will have an account which is a ledger<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT>, or off<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT>, account within the Binance system with a unique identifier and associated login credentials, against which the relevant user credit balances are recorded. Binance is not a trustee of, and does not owe any trustee duties in relation to, any cryptocurrency assets held to our credit. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We maintain our cryptocurrency assets with third<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-party</FONT> custodians or exchanges that do not carry insurance or do not disclose whether carrying insurance for any losses of the cryptocurrency assets, exposing us to a material loss of these assets in the event of a security breach, operational failure, or insolvency of such custodian&#x201d; and &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our limited visibility into Binance&#x2019;s custody practices restricts our ability to verify or control the safeguarding of our cryptocurrency assets held on Binance, which could result in a material loss of our holdings.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Risks and Challenges</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Investing in our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares entails a significant level of risk. Before investing in our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares, you should carefully consider the risks and uncertainties summarized below, the risks described under the &#x201c;Risk Factors,&#x201d; in addition to all of the other information in this prospectus and documents that are incorporated in this prospectus, as updated by our subsequent filings under the Securities Exchange&#x00a0;Act&#x00a0;of&#x00a0;1934, as amended (the &#x201c;Exchange&#x00a0;Act&#x201d;), and, if applicable, in any accompanying prospectus supplement or documents incorporated by reference. The occurrence of one or more of the events or circumstances described in the section titled &#x201c;Risk Factors,&#x201d; and those included in the accompanying prospectus and the documents incorporated by reference herein and therein, alone or in combination with other events or circumstances, may adversely affect our business, results of operations and financial condition. Such risks include, but are not limited to:</P>
		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Risks Related to this Offering</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Volatile trading price of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to this Offering&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;The trading price of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares is likely to be volatile, which could result in substantial losses to investors&#x201d; and &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to this Offering&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Sales of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares, or the perception of such sales, by the selling shareholders pursuant to this prospectus in the public market or otherwise could cause the market price for our Class&#x00a0;A Ordinary Shares to decline.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Risks related to the use of proceeds. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to this Offering&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We have not determined a specific use for a portion of the net proceeds from the securities offering, and we may use these proceeds in ways with which you may not agree.&#x201d;</P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">3</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Risks Related to Our Business</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Uncertainties in our research and development activities. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Business&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We may fail to anticipate or adapt to technology innovations in a timely manner, so our IC design may fail to gain recognition from the customers and the IC design industry&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Volatility of the cryptocurrency market. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Business&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our results of operations have been and are expected to continue to be significantly impacted by the volatility of the cryptocurrency market, and in particular, the sharp price decrease of cryptocurrencies&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>, &#x201c;We face significant risks relating to our reliance on third<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-party</FONT> quantitative trading teams for the custody and trading of our cryptocurrencies, including risks related to market volatility and forced liquidation, trading system and API, counterparty and agency, team competency and trading system, instability of profitability, and arbitrage trading, which could materially and adversely impact our business, financial condition and results of operations&#x201d; in the current reports on Form&#x00a0;6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT> furnished with the SEC on June<FONT CLASS="nobreak">&#x00a0;</FONT>24, 2025 (the &#x201c;June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>&#x201d;) and &#x201c;Market manipulation activities within the cryptocurrency market may materially disrupt market integrity, reduce liquidity, and cause significant price volatility, adversely impacting our trading operations, revenue generation, and business, financial condition and results of operations&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Network security of cryptocurrencies. See &#x201c;We face significant risks relating to disruptions, forks, 51% attacks, hacks, network disruptions, or other adverse events or other compromises to the cryptocurrency blockchains, which could materially and adversely impact our business, financial condition and results of operations&#x201d; and &#x201c;We face risks relating to the potential compromise of Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies&#x2019; network security by emerging technologies, including artificial intelligence and quantum computing, which may materially and adversely impact our operations and financial condition&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Uncertainty of the regulation on cryptocurrencies and relevant transaction and trading venue related risks. See &#x201c;Cryptocurrencies, including Bitcoin, face significant scaling obstacles that can lead to high fees or slow transaction settlement times&#x201d;, &#x201c;Bitcoin and other digital assets are novel assets, and are subject to significant legal, commercial, regulatory and technical uncertainty&#x201d;, &#x201c;The due diligence procedures conducted by us and our liquidity provider to mitigate transaction risk may fail to prevent transactions with bad actors that have used cryptocurrencies to launder money&#x201d;, &#x201c;Banks and financial institutions may not provide banking services, or may cut off services, to businesses that engage in crypto<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-related</FONT> activities&#x201d;, &#x201c;Due to the unregulated nature and lack of transparency surrounding the operations of many trading venues Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies we hold, these trading venues may experience greater fraud, security failures or regulatory or operational problems than trading venues for more established asset classes, which may result in a loss of confidence in such trading venues and adversely affect the value of Bitcoin or other cryptocurrencies we hold&#x201d; and &#x201c;We are not subject to legal and regulatory obligations that apply to investment companies such as mutual funds and exchange<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-traded</FONT> funds, or to obligations applicable to investment advisers&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Risks related to stablecoins. See &#x201c;We are exposed to risks related to the custody, transaction and issuance of stablecoins, which could materially and adversely affect our business, financial condition and results of operations&#x201d;, &#x201c;As a relatively new innovation, stablecoins are particularly susceptible to operational challenges and risks, including due to surges in demand&#x201d; and &#x201c;The acceptance of stablecoins could be negatively impacted by the disruptions in secondary marketplace, which could negatively affect our business, financial condition and results of operations&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Price volatility of cryptocurrencies. See &#x201c;Cryptocurrency price volatility may materially depress asset valuations, necessitating substantial cash reserves or liquidity buffers to maintain operational resilience. These risks are compounded by the lack of comprehensive regulation governing cryptocurrency trading platforms, which face material exposure to fraud, market manipulation, security breaches, and operational failures that could materially and adversely affect the value of our small<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-cap</FONT> cryptocurrency holdings&#x201d; and &#x201c;The emergence or growth of other digital assets, including those with significant private or public sector backing, could have a negative impact on the price of Bitcoin or other cryptocurrencies we hold and adversely affect our business&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">4</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Risks related to custodially<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-held</FONT> cryptocurrencies. See &#x201c;Our custodially<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-held</FONT> Bitcoin or other cryptocurrencies may become part of the custodian&#x2019;s insolvency estate if one or more of our custodians enters bankruptcy, receivership or similar insolvency proceedings&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Market conditions for HTC and HPC solutions market. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Business&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We have derived and may continue to derive revenues primarily from our HTC and HPC solutions. If the market for HTC and HPC solutions ceases to exist or diminishes significantly, our business, results of operations and financial condition would be materially and adversely affected&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Constant technological changes in the industries we operate in. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Business&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our business growth is dependent on the development of blockchain technology and applications, particularly in the field of Bitcoin, ETC, Grin and Filecoin&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Significant revenue contribution from our cryptocurrency mining machines. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Business&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;If cryptocurrencies relating to our products lose their popularity or are replaced by other cryptocurrencies as the mainstream cryptocurrencies, we may not be able to win the market for our future mining machines and our results of operations will be materially and adversely affected&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT> and &#x201c;We face significant risks relating to income concentration in limited blockchain partners and associated disclosure deficiencies which may trigger regulatory actions or litigation&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Our reliance on limited suppliers. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Business&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our IC products mainly depend on supplies from third<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-party</FONT> foundries, and any failure to obtain sufficient foundry capacity from such foundries would significantly delay the shipment of our products&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Risks Related to Our Operations</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Our ability to achieve or sustain profitability. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We have incurred net losses and negative cash flows from operating activities in the past, and we may not achieve or sustain profitability&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Our ability to forecast our business and assess the seasonality and volatility in our business. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our limited operating history and our volatile historical results of operations could make it difficult for us to forecast our business and assess the seasonality and volatility in our business&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT> and &#x201c;We face significant risks relating to the ongoing evolution of our business model and inherent future uncertainties, which could materially impair our ability to execute our strategy, achieve profitability, and adversely affect our business, financial condition and results of operations&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Our ability to obtain significant financial resources. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our business requires significant financial resources, but we may not be able to obtain it in a timely manner and on favorable terms or at all&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Our ability to price our products at our desired margins. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We may not be able to price our products at our desired margins as a result of any decrease in our bargaining power or changes in market conditions&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Credit risks and concentration of credit risks in relation to defaults from counterparties. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We may be exposed to credit risks and concentration of credit risks in relation to defaults from counterparties&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Our ability to manage our growth or execute our strategies effectively. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;If we are unable to manage our growth or execute our strategies effectively, our business, results of operations and financial condition may be materially and adversely affected&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
