	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Ongoing global coronavirus COVID<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-19</FONT> outbreak. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our business, results of operations and financial position could be adversely affected by the ongoing COVID<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-19</FONT> pandemic&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>High customer concentration. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;High customer concentration exposes us to all of the risks faced by our major customers and may subject us to significant fluctuations or declines in revenues&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Liquidity risk in relation to cryptocurrencies. See &#x201c;Our cryptocurrency holdings are less liquid than our existing cash and cash equivalents and may not be able to serve as a source of liquidity for us to the same extent as cash and cash equivalents&#x201d; in the June&#x00a0;24 6<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Volatility in BNB market price risks. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Significant volatility in the market price of BNB may cause material losses and adversely affect our financial position.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Dependence of BNB value on Binance&#x2019;s operations. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;BNB&#x2019;s value and utility are heavily dependent on the ongoing operation, success, and reputation of Binance and its affiliates, exposing our reserves to material devaluation.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Concentration risk in BNB reserves. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Significant concentration of reserve value in BNB amplifies exposure to token<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-specific</FONT> failures. Competition and potential technological obsolescence may adversely impact BNB&#x2019;s value.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Liquidity challenges for BNB holdings. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our BNB holdings may face unique liquidity challenges or devaluation due to concentration or market perception. Liquidity constraints may prevent us from converting BNB holdings into fiat currency or stable value when needed, or without significant losses.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Technical and security risks to BNB ecosystem. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Technical flaws, security breaches, or failures within the BNB blockchain ecosystem could impair the utility value of our BNB holdings.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Limited visibility into Binance&#x2019;s custody practices. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our limited visibility into Binance&#x2019;s custody practices restricts our ability to verify or control the safeguarding of our cryptocurrency assets held on Binance, which could result in a material loss of our holdings.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Lack of insurance in relation to our cryptocurrency assets. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We maintain our cryptocurrency assets with third<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-party</FONT> custodians or exchanges that do not carry insurance or do not disclose whether carrying insurance for any losses of the cryptocurrency assets, exposing us to a material loss of these assets in the event of a security breach, operational failure, or insolvency of such custodian.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Risks Related to Our Industry</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Adverse changes in the regulatory environment in China. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Industry&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;It may be or become illegal to acquire, own, hold, sell or use cryptocurrencies, participate in the blockchain, transfer or utilize similar bitcoin assets in China or overseas markets where we operate due to adverse changes in the regulatory and policy environment in these jurisdictions&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Adverse changes of regulatory environment in foreign markets. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Industry&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;The current regulatory environment in foreign markets, including the United&#x00a0;States, and any adverse changes in that environment, could have a material adverse impact on our blockchain products business&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">6</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Increasing mining difficulty, which could result in downward pressure on the expected economic returns. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Industry&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Increasing mining difficulty could result in downward pressure on the expected economic returns on cryptocurrency mining&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Concert actions, which could prevent new transactions from gaining confirmations, halt payments between users, and reverse previously completed transactions. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Industry&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;If any person, institution or a pool of them acting in concert obtains control of more than 50% of the processing power active on the Bitcoin, Ethereum Classic or Grin, such person, institution or a pool of them could prevent new transactions from gaining confirmations, halt payments between users, and reverse previously completed transactions, which would erode user confidence in Bitcoin, Ethereum Classic or Grin&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Challenges against decentralized nature of cryptocurrencies. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Industry&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;The decentralized nature of cryptocurrency may be subject to challenges, which could negatively affect our results of operations&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Change of algorithm and mining mechanism. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Industry&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Change of algorithm and mining mechanism for cryptocurrencies may materially and adversely affect our business and results of operations&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Risks Related to Conducting Business in China</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Exposure to PRC government influence. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;The PRC government has significant authority to exert influence on the China operations of an offshore holding company, and offerings conducted overseas and foreign investment in China<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT> issuers, such as us. Changes in China&#x2019;s economic, political or social conditions or government policies could have a material adverse effect on our business, results of operations, financial condition, and the value of our securities.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Uncertainties in China&#x2019;s legal and regulatory environment. See &#x201c;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Operations&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Uncertainties with respect to the enforcement of and changes in laws and regulations in China could have a material adverse effect on our business, results of operations, financial condition and future prospects, and cause our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares to significantly decline in value or become worthless.&#x201d;</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Recent regulatory developments in China, which may subject us to additional regulatory review. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Conducting Business in China&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Recent regulatory developments in China may subject us to additional regulatory review or otherwise restrict or completely hinder our ability to offer securities and raise capitals overseas, all of which could materially and adversely affect our business and cause the value of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares to significantly decline or become worthless&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Significant influence of PRC government over companies with China<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT> operations. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Conducting Business in China&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;The PRC government has significant influence over companies with China<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT> operations by enforcing existing rules and regulation, adopting new ones, or changing relevant industrial policies in a manner that may materially increase our compliance cost, change relevant industry landscape or otherwise cause significant changes to our operations in China, which could result in material and adverse changes in our operations and cause the value of our securities to significantly decline or be worthless&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Possibility of delisting if the PCAOB is unable to inspect auditors with presence in China. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Conducting Business in China&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares will be delisted and prohibited from trading in the over<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-the</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-counter</FONT> market under the Holding Foreign Companies Accountable Act, if the PCAOB is unable to inspect or investigate completely auditors located in China for two consecutive&#x00a0;years. The delisting of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares, or the threat of their being delisted, may materially and adversely affect the value of your investment&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">7</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Changes in the political and economic policies of the PRC government. 		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Uncertainties regarding the interpretation and enforcement of PRC laws, rules and regulations. 		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>A severe or prolonged downturn in China&#x2019;s economy. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. 		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Increased labor costs and enforcement of stricter labor laws and regulations in China. 		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Risks Related to Our Corporate Structure and Governance</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Investors in our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares not purchasing equity securities of our subsidiaries that have substantive business operations in China but instead equity securities of a Cayman Islands holding company. 		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Custodians or authorized users of our controlling non<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-tangible</FONT> assets, including chops and seals, failing to fulfill their responsibilities. 		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Anti<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-takeover</FONT> provisions in our currently effective memorandum and articles of association. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. 		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Dual<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-class</FONT> structure of our ordinary shares which could affect the trading market for our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. 		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Less protection to shareholders due to our home country practices for corporate governance matters. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Corporate Structure and Governance&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;You may face difficulties in protecting your interests, and your ability to protect your rights through U.S.&#x00a0;courts may be limited, because we are incorporated under Cayman Islands law and conduct our operations primarily in emerging markets&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Certain judgments obtained against us by our shareholders may not be enforceable. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. 		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;list-style-type:none;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Reduced reporting requirements due to our emerging growth company status. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Corporate Structure and Governance&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We are an emerging growth company within the meaning of the Securities Act and may take advantage of certain reduced reporting requirements&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Our exemption from certain provisions applicable to U.S.&#x00a0;domestic public companies due to our foreign private issuer status. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Our Corporate Structure and Governance&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;We are a foreign private issuer within the meaning of the rules under the Exchange&#x00a0;Act, and as such we are exempt from certain provisions applicable to United&#x00a0;States domestic public companies&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="H3" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="BoldItalic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Risks Related to our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Failure to maintain the listing of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares with a U.S.&#x00a0;national securities exchange. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;If we fail to maintain the listing of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares with a U.S.&#x00a0;national securities exchange, the liquidity and price of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares could be adversely affected&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Lack of research or report on the business or change in recommendations regarding our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;If securities or industry analysts do not publish research or reports about our business, or if they adversely change their recommendations regarding our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares, the market price for our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares and trading volume could decline&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="BL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;list-style-position:outside;list-style-type:disc;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="bullet" STYLE="font-size:10pt;">&#x2022;<FONT STYLE="width: 27px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT></FONT>Sale or availability for sale of substantial amounts of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;The sale or availability for sale of substantial amounts of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares could adversely affect their market price&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Potential CAC and CSRC Approval Required for Offerings under this Prospectus</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The General Office of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and the General Office of the State Council jointly issued the Opinions on Severe and Lawful Crackdown on Illegal Securities Activities, which was available to the public on July&#x00a0;6, 2021. These opinions emphasized the need to strengthen the administration over illegal securities activities and the supervision on overseas listings by China<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT> companies. These opinions proposed to take effective measures, such as promoting the construction of relevant regulatory systems to deal with the risks and incidents facing China<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT> overseas<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-listed</FONT> companies and the demand for cybersecurity and data privacy protection. Moreover, on January&#x00a0;4, 2022, the CAC, and other ministries and commissions (including the CSRC), announced the adoption of the Cybersecurity Review Measures, which became effective on February&#x00a0;15, 2022 and provides that network platform operators possessing personal information of more than one million individual users must undergo a cybersecurity review by the CAC when they seek to have their securities listed on a foreign stock exchange. Furthermore, the Standing Committee of the National People&#x2019;s Congress passed the Personal Information Protection Law of the PRC (&#x201c;PIPL&#x201d;), which became effective on November&#x00a0;1, 2021, requires such operators to obtain consent of the user prior to any cross<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-border</FONT> transfer of personal information, as well as the satisfaction of at least one of the following conditions: (1)&#x00a0;a security assessment organized by competent cybersecurity authorities has been passed; (2)&#x00a0;certification of personal information protection from a specialized institution in accordance with the provisions issued by competent cybersecurity authorities has been passed; (3)&#x00a0;a model standard contract about both parties&#x2019; rights and obligations formulated by competent cybersecurity authorities with the overseas recipient has been entered into; or (4)&#x00a0;any other condition prescribed by laws, administrative regulations or by competent cybersecurity authorities has been satisfied. These policies and any related implementation rules to be enacted may subject us to additional compliance requirement. As of the date of this prospectus, no official guidance or related implementation rules have been issued in relation to these issued opinions, and the interpretation and implementation of these opinions remain unclear at this stage. Moreover, the M&amp;A Rules requires an overseas special purpose vehicle that are controlled by PRC companies or individuals formed for the purpose of seeking a public listing on an overseas stock exchange through acquisitions of PRC domestic companies using shares of such special purpose vehicle or held by its shareholders as considerations to obtain the approval of the CSRC, prior to the listing and trading of such special purpose vehicle&#x2019;s securities on an overseas stock exchange. However, the application of the M&amp;A Rules remains unclear.</P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">9</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">In recent&#x00a0;years, the PRC government initiated a series of regulatory actions and made a number of public statements on the regulation of business operations in China with little advance notice, including cracking down on illegal activities in the securities market, enhancing supervision over China<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT> companies listed overseas, adopting new measures to extend the scope of cybersecurity reviews, and expanding efforts in anti<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-monopoly</FONT> enforcement. The PRC government also exerts more control over offerings conducted overseas and foreign investment in China<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT> issuers. In particular, on February&#x00a0;17, 2023, the CSRC released the Trial Measures, which came into effect on March&#x00a0;31, 2023. The Trial Measures apply to overseas securities offerings and/or listings conducted by (1)&#x00a0;companies incorporated in the PRC, or PRC domestic companies, directly and (2)&#x00a0;companies incorporated overseas with operations primarily in the PRC and valued on the basis of interests in PRC domestic companies, or indirect offerings. The Trial Measures requires (i)&#x00a0;the filings of the overseas offering and listing plan by the PRC domestic companies with the CSRC under certain conditions, and (ii)&#x00a0;the filing of their underwriters or placement agents with the CSRC under certain conditions and the submission of an annual report to the CSRC within the required timeline. On the same&#x00a0;day, the Provisions on Strengthening Confidentiality and Archives Administration of Overseas Securities Offering and Listing by Domestic Companies (the &#x201c;Confidentiality and Archives Administration Provisions&#x201d;) promulgated by the CSRC came into effect. Confidentiality and Archives Administration Provisions stipulate that the PRC companies seeking overseas offerings and listings, either directly or indirectly, as well as securities firms and securities service providers (both the PRC and overseas) involved in relevant businesses, must not disclose any state secrets or confidential information of government agencies, nor harm national security and public interests. Additionally, if a domestic company provides accounting archives or copies of such archives to any entities, including securities firms, securities service providers, overseas regulators and individuals, it must comply with due procedures in accordance with applicable regulations. We believe that offerings under this prospectus do not involve the disclosure of any state secret or confidential information of government agencies, nor does it harm national security and public interests. However, we may need to perform additional procedures concerning the provision of accounting archives. The specific requirements of these procedures are currently unclear, and we cannot guarantee our ability to execute them. According to the Notice on Overseas Listing Measures published by the CSRC on February&#x00a0;17, 2023, issuers that had already been listed in an overseas market by March&#x00a0;31, 2023, the date the Trial Measures became effective, are not required to make any immediate filing and are only required to comply with the filing requirements under the Trial Measures when it subsequently seeks to conduct a follow<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-on</FONT> offering. Therefore, we are required to go through filing procedures with the CSRC within three working&#x00a0;days after the completion of the Private Placement and for our future offerings of our securities in an overseas market, including Nasdaq, under the Trial Measures. Other than the CSRC filing procedure we are required to make within three working&#x00a0;days after the completion of the Private Placement, we and our PRC subsidiaries, as advised our PRC legal counsel, Zhong Lun Law Firm, (1)&#x00a0;are not required to obtain permissions from the CSRC, and (2)&#x00a0;have not been required to obtain or denied such and other permissions by the CSRC, CAC, or any PRC government authority, under current PRC laws, regulations and rules in connection with the Private Placement or a potential resale made by the selling shareholders pursuant to this prospectus as of the date of this prospectus. See &#x201c;Item&#x00a0;3. Key Information&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;D.&#x00a0;Risk Factors&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Risks Related to Conducting Business in China&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;Recent regulatory developments in China may subject us to additional regulatory review or otherwise restrict or completely hinder our ability to offer securities and raise capitals overseas, all of which could materially and adversely affect our business and cause the value of our Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares to significantly decline or become worthless&#x201d; in the 2024 20<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-F</FONT>.</P>
		<P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Corporate History and Structure</FONT></P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">We are a Cayman Islands holding company and primarily conduct our operations in China through our PRC subsidiaries. We first started our business designing and developing high throughput computing solutions through Zhejiang Haowei Technology Co., Ltd., or Zhejiang Haowei, incorporated in July&#x00a0;2019. Since our inception, we have been devoted to the design and development of computing power solutions.</P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">10</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>






	<DIV CLASS="BOXSTYLE" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-color:#000000;border-width:1pt;border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding: 10.0pt 4.0pt 10.0pt 4.0pt;">
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">On January&#x00a0;8, 2021, we incorporated Nano Labs Ltd, our holding company, as an exempted company with limited liability under the laws of the Cayman Islands. In 2021, we underwent a series of corporate reorganization in anticipation of our initial public offering, including incorporation of our company as the listing vehicle, incorporation of our oversea holding companies and issuance of shares to shareholders of Zhejiang Haowei. In May&#x00a0;2021, we completed a one<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-for</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-10</FONT>,000<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>shares subdivision, following which our authorized share capital of US$50,000 is divided into 500,000,000 ordinary shares of US$0.0001 each.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">On July&#x00a0;12, 2022, our American depositary shares representing Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares commenced trading on the Nasdaq Global Market under the symbol of &#x201c;NA.&#x201d; On December&#x00a0;29, 2023, Citibank N.A. distributed a notification regarding the amendment to the deposit agreement, dated December&#x00a0;19, 2023, as amended, and the termination of American depositary receipts facility for our American depositary shares, effective from February&#x00a0;1, 2024.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Effective from January&#x00a0;31, 2024, we conducted a 2<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-to-1</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>share consolidation, which consolidated two shares with a par value of US$0.0001 each in our issued and unissued share capital into one share with a par value of US$0.0002. Upon the effectiveness of such share consolidation, our authorized share capital became US$50,000 divided into 250,000,000 ordinary shares of par value of US$0.0002 each, comprising (1)&#x00a0;121,410,923 Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares of par value of US$0.0002 each, (2)&#x00a0;28,589,078 Class&#x00a0;B ordinary shares of par value of US$0.0002 each and (3)&#x00a0;99,999,999<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>shares of a par value of US$0.0002 each of such class or classes (however designated) as our board of directors may determine in accordance with our memorandum and articles of association, as amended. Effective from November&#x00a0;3, 2024, we conducted a 10<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-to-1</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>share consolidation, which consolidated 10<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>shares with a par value of US$0.0002 each in our issued and unissued share capital into one share with a par value of US$0.002. Upon the effectiveness of such share consolidation, our authorized share capital became US$50,000 divided into 25,000,000 ordinary shares of par value of US$0.002 each, comprising (1)&#x00a0;12,141,093 Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares of par value of US$0.002 each, (2)&#x00a0;2,858,908 Class&#x00a0;B ordinary shares of par value of US$0.002 each, and (3)&#x00a0;9,999,999<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>shares of a par value of US$0.002 each of such class or classes (however designated) as our board of directors may determine in accordance with our memorandum and articles of association, as amended. Unless otherwise indicated, shares and per share amount in this annual report represent the actual ones at the relevant time. Effective from 18 December&#x00a0;2024, we re<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-designated</FONT> 2,000,000 undesignated shares as Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares. Upon the effectiveness of such share re<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-designation</FONT>, our authorized share capital became US$50,000 divided into 25,000,000 ordinary shares of par value of US$0.002 each, comprising (1)&#x00a0;14,141,093 Class&#x00a0;A Ordinary Shares of par value of US$0.002 each, (2)&#x00a0;2,858,909 Class&#x00a0;B Ordinary Shares of par value of US$0.002 each and (3)&#x00a0;7,999,998<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>shares of a par value of US$0.002 each of such class or classes (however designated) as the board of directors may determine in accordance with our memorandum and articles of association, as amended.</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_ind" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">On March&#x00a0;7, 2025, we (1)&#x00a0;increased the authorized share capital from US$50,000 divided into 25,000,000 ordinary shares of par value of US$0.002 each to US$4,200,000 dividing into 2,100,000,000<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>shares with a par value of US$0.002 each, comprising 1,097,141,091 Class&#x00a0;A ordinary shares, 2,858,909 Class&#x00a0;B ordinary shares, and 1,000,000,000<FONT CLASS="nobreak"> </FONT>shares of a par value of US$0.002 each of such class or classes (however designated) as our board of directors may determine in accordance with our memorandum and articles of association, as amended; and (2)&#x00a0;increased the votes per Class&#x00a0;B ordinary share from 15 to 30.</P>
		</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">11</P>
